oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Evaluation of Four Therapies of Papillomatous Digital Dermatitis in Dairy Cattle

lesions

oai_dc:dc.dc:description: One hundred and forty-seven Holstein cows in three Central California dairy herds, housed in open corrals with shades, with active Papillomatous Digital Dermatitis (hairy footwart) lesions were randomly assigned to one of five treatment groups.
